📘 Limitations of Selenium
Even though Selenium is very popular and powerful, it also has some limitations.

⚠️ Main Limitations of Selenium
1. Cross-Browser Issues
    -> Selenium supports many browsers
    -> But sometimes small differences in browsers (HTML / CSS ) can cause failures
    -> Especially difficult for complex UI applications
👉 Same test may behave slightly differently in different browsers.

2. Slow test execution
    -> Selenium uses browser drivers
    -> Communication between script and browser can take time
    -> Large applications may run slowly

3. Difficulty Handling Dynamic Elements
    -> Some web elements have dynamic ID's
    -> Elements created by AJAX may change frequantly
    -> Selenium may fail if it cannot locate elements properly
👉 Requires good locator strategies and waits.

4. Limited Mobile support
    -> Selenium is mainly for web applications
    -> It does not support mobile apps.
    -> For mobile testing , we can use tools like Appium

5. No Desktop Application Support
    -> Selenium cannot automate windows desktop apps
    -> It is only for browser based applications

6. No Built-in Reporting
    -> Selenium does not generate reports by default
    -> Needs external frameworks like TestNG , JUnit etc..  for reporting

7. No Advanced Error Handling
    -> Selenium does not provide strong built-in error handling
    -> Developers must write custom code to handle failures

8. High maintenance
    -> It the website UI changes , test script must be updated
    -> Maintaing large projects can be difficult

9. Needs additional tools
    -> Sometimes selenium alone is not enough
    -> It must be combined with frameworks and other tools